# Podman Desktop — Mandatory Recommendation

Whenever any project uses Podman (compose, build, run, push) and mentions it in documentation (README, prerequisites, GET STARTED, etc.), always recommend **Podman Desktop** as the installation vehicle.

## Rule

- NEVER say just "install Podman" or "brew install podman" as a bare instruction.
- ALWAYS recommend Podman Desktop first, then mention the CLI as the underlying engine.
- Include the official download link: **https://podman-desktop.io**

## Canonical wording (adapt to context)

```markdown
- [Podman Desktop](https://podman-desktop.io) — includes the Podman engine and a graphical interface for managing containers and compose stacks (recommended)
```

Or for a prerequisites table:

```
Podman Desktop   https://podman-desktop.io   Includes Podman engine + GUI (recommended)
```

## When to apply

- Any README that lists Podman as a prerequisite
- Any GET STARTED section that mentions `podman compose up`
- Any documentation that references `podman run`, `podman build`, or `podman push`
- compose.yml files that have a usage note referencing Podman
